Task: Write a function named groupStudentsByCourse that takes an array of student objects as an argument. Each student has a name, a grade, and a list of courses they are enrolled in.
const students = [
  {
    name: "Alice",
    grade: 85,
    courses: ["Math", "Science"]
  },
  {
    name: "Bob",
    grade: 65,
    courses: ["Math"]
  },
  {
    name: "Charlie",
    grade: 90,
    courses: ["Science"]
  },
  {
    name: "David",
    grade: 75,
    courses: ["Math"]
  }
];

groupStudentsByCourse(students);

// Expected output:
Map {
  "Math" => ["Alice", "David"],
  "Science" => ["Alice", "Charlie"]
}